news.title: Noida: Cameras at building sites, washing of roads when GRAP kicks in
news.para: In stage 1, CAQM has suggested dust mitigation, checking municipal, C&D and hazardous waste, water sprinkling and mechanised sweeping of roads, and use of anti-smoke guns at construction sites, among others.

news.title: GRAP: Municipal corporation of Delhi looks to rein in disposal of C&D waste
news.para: While sanctioning the building plans of such properties, MCD has asked them to adhere to the norms for dumping construction and demolition waste.

news.title: GRAP: Six teams set up in Gurugram to keep bad air in check, violators to face heavy fines
news.para: The department of town and country planning (DTCP) has also constituted three teams, with two members each, to enforce dust control rules during construction activities and shut down non-compliant sites.
